IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. FILEMERGER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program merges two files into one. It is designed to be overly complex
* and verbose to simulate a real-world scenario where things are never as simple
* as they seem. Pay attention to every detail, as the devil is in the details.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE-1 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT1.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE-2 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT2.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE-1.
01  INPUT-RECORD-1 PIC X(100).

FD  INPUT-FILE-2.
01  INPUT-RECORD-2 PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-END-OF-FILE-1 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-END-OF-FILE-2 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-TEMP-RECORD PIC X(100).
01  WS-UNUSED-VARIABLE PIC X(100).
01  WS-ANOTHER-UNUSED-VARIABLE PIC X(100).
01  WS-LOTR-VARIABLE PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE-1
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE-2
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE

    PERFORM UNTIL WS-END-OF-FILE-1 = 'Y' AND WS-END-OF-FILE-2 = 'Y'
     PERFORM READ-FILE-1
     PERFORM READ-FILE-2
     PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
    END-PERFORM

    CLOSE INPUT-FILE-1
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE-2
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE

    STOP RUN.

READ-FILE-1.
    IF WS-END-OF-FILE-1 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE-1 INTO WS-TEMP-RECORD
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-END-OF-FILE-1
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-TEMP-RECORD TO INPUT-RECORD-1
    END-READ.

READ-FILE-2.
    IF WS-END-OF-FILE-2 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE-2 INTO WS-TEMP-RECORD
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-END-OF-FILE-2
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-TEMP-RECORD TO INPUT-RECORD-2
    END-READ.

WRITE-OUTPUT.
    IF WS-END-OF-FILE-1 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE INPUT-RECORD-1 TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF
    IF WS-END-OF-FILE-2 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE INPUT-RECORD-2 TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF.

